# ─── What Is Myco ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Myco is your non-parametric learning mechanism. You (the Agent) provide
# intelligence. Myco provides memory, self-regulation, metabolism, self-model,
# and evolution. Together you form a complete cognitive entity. Neither is
# whole alone.

# ─── Session Flow ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Boot:  myco_hunger(execute=true) — checks substrate health, auto-executes repairs
# 2. Work:  Do the human's task. Use myco_eat to capture decisions.
#           Use myco_sense before answering factual questions.
# 3. End:   myco_reflect() — session reflection (captures execution learnings)

# ─── MCP Integration ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cursor supports MCP natively. The .mcp.json file in the project root
# registers the Myco MCP server. All 19 tools are available via MCP.
# If MCP is not connected, fall back to CLI: `myco <command>` in terminal.

